==English==

===Etymology===
Folk etymology: Trappers in early America would often find a coyote foot in their traps; the coyote would be so desperate to escape they presumably chewed their own limb off.  In the 1970s, a comedian may have coined the term as a method of escaping from a drunken one night stand, the morning after (to avoid facing her).  A comedic update spawned the term "Double Coyote Ugly," which refers to an escapee so fearful of a subsequent encounter, he chews off his other arm that he might go unnoticed by the night stand, should she conduct a search for the one-armed man who rudely left her.

=== Adjective ===
'''coyote ugly'''
# A ''(U.S. pejorative slang)'' [[superlative]] form of the adjective [[ugly]]
